items.name: Ambience - SDXL
items.description:
💚 for Updates - I would love to see your reviews and images of this model, feel free to post them below!

Ambience is currently an experimental test model that aims to replicate the creativity and styling of Maverick using the SDXL 1.0 base. I'm currently unable to test and operate these models as I would normally on Automatic1111 and have recently tried out Comfy UI to be able to run XL base models.

💡 This model is currently an experimental project

  • expected to change a good amount from version to version.

  • testing is currently slow, limited, & inefficient.

  • if possible with my gpu/vram, I would like to look into training some simple elements to merge in. I may look into Google Colab as an option as well.

  • I'm hoping to get XL based models functioning on A1111 for better testing and familiar workflow.

  • current aim is to merge in more raw elements, sharpen things a bit with clarity to get rid of the rough/feathery aesthetic with the XL base model currently, improving backgrounds/scenery, clean up any detail inaccuracies where I can.

Recommended Use

Unknown for the most part at the moment. Below are a few example workflows using ComfyUI. I have been using the SDXL base refiner, but this may not even be needed. You can also try using a refine element with the model itself, a SD 1.5 base model, or a similar XL model. I have not been able to try any hires fix options and haven't done much upscaling where I'm able to try denoising parameters etc.

Currently I've been using
~30 steps, 7 scale, DPM++ SDE Karras, Euler a, or a mixture of the two split between base model/refiner

You can try other samplers as well. DPM++ 2M Karras and Euler seemed to be decent too. I'm not really sure how a clip skip parameter is replicated in Comfy UI at the moment. CFG Scale I have been fine with at 7, you can try higher or lower and try splitting different variables between base model/refiner if used. Step count I have kept at mostly 30, 20-50 probably seem good. Feel free to see what works best with other parameters.

Negative embeddings are not needed. I have used some here and there and they seem to work fine. You may find positives or negatives with them depending on use.

Workflow Examples

The preview images should have workflows/metadata built in and should be viewable by dragging into your interface (Comfy ui, A1111, etc.). Having just tried out Comfy ui myself recently, you may find you have a more adequate workflow(s).

  • Example 1 (slightly rearranged, adds additional quality tags within the workflow - you can change these to best match your styling, initially via KidCharles)

  • Example 2 (workflow from the SDXL page, via StabilityAI or Civitai)

  • Example 3 (simple SDXL workflow, via Comfy ui creator? unknown source)

There are also many great Comfy ui workflows listed on Civitai, plugins, etc. Such as ones geared toward 4GB vram cards. Try filtering to the 'other' category and/or searching for them with SDXL/workflow keyword(s).

Disclaimer

This model(s) may output NSFW content unintentionally depending on parameters used. Make sure you tailor your prompts accordingly. For example "nsfw" in the negative prompt.

The purpose of sharing this model is not to showcase obscene material in a public forum. The use of this learning model is entirely at the discretion of the user, and they have the freedom to choose whether or not to create SFW or NSFW content. The decision of whether to engage with SFW or NSFW content lies with the user and their own personal preferences. The AI model(s) do not contain explicit visual content that can be accessed easily.

Note: this is a general disclaimer, I have not experienced any nsfw content popping up with SDXL based models thus far.

Resources

This model merge (a1) used the following resources - all of these are great stand-alone, props to each creator.

  • MBBXL Alpha_v0.1 (via morbuto)
    note: 'no sharing merges' is now listed on v1.0RC and was not present on the model page with v0.1, I do not plan to use any versions of this going forward.

items.description:
This is a retrain of my Rei Ayanami in mogudan's style LORA Seems some of the tweaks to balance the outfits caused a bit of a training time inflation. This should have come after the V2 of the LORA but it is what it is. The V1 LORA is nice and probably a bit more flexible that this one. But Having a LORA spit out the correct outfits on demand has it's own charm.

Works fine with: <lora:Ayanami_Rei_MogudanV3:0.7> ayanami_rei_mogudan, huge breasts, <outfit>

As Always i left her breasts size toggleable for the weird rando out there who wishes to desecrate her boobs and make them smaller. You know who you are and you should be ashamed of yourself! :P

I isolated the following outfits, they are of course Mogudan variants:

  • Mogudan_MicroSkirt_Suspender_skirt_School_Uniform: Mogudan's take on the Tokyo 3 uniform.

items.name: Belle Delphine XL
items.description:
This is a LoRA of the internet celebrity Belle Delphine for Stable Diffusion XL. (For my previous LoRA for 1.5 based checkpoints see here.)

 

This LoRA is quite flexible, but this should be mostly thanks to SDXL, not really my specific training.

As trigger word "Belle Delphine" is used. Additionally, “braces” has been tagged a few times in the source images, so you might also be able to use this as a tag during generation.

I suggest a default LoRA weight of 1.

I tested this LoRA with the base model + refiner, but I wasn’t really happy with that, as the refiner removed characteristics again.

Most images were generated with DreamShaper XL1.0 Alpha2.

Additionally tested were Tdg8uU's SDXL1.0 mix and Anime Art Diffusion XL (the last 4 wide images are 4 different models).

 

These images have been rendered using ComfyUI using quite a high-fidelity workflow (also depending on the image). But you can assume results were produced with a 1024x1024 base resolution (with different aspect ratio), then latent based img2img upscale with a factor of 1.5 and then also using ComfyUI-Impact-Pack for face details (if needed). The workflow should be embedded with the example images. It should work at >= 8GB VRAM. To make use of it you will need the following custom ComfyUI nodes:

  • ComfyUI-Impact-Pack

  • Automatic Sizing for SDXL

  • WAS Node Suite (only really used to save images with a timestamp, besides that not used)

 

Training:

I assume some people might be interested in how this was trained, but I will have to disappoint you, as it was my first try with default settings and I am sufficiently happy with it, so no secret tips. In detail I used the following base configuration file.

With those settings I used 151 uncropped, manually captioned high resolution images with bucketing in the resolution range 512-2048, 32 as bucket steps. The image dataset was set for 25 repetitions, additionally there was a regularization dataset (freshly generated with SDXL) with about 3000 images, set to 2 repetitions. Originally, I set training to 30 epochs (as that was the default of the previous mentioned config file), but around 8 epochs the results began to overbake. For that reason I stopped after 18 epochs (around 27000 steps). The final LoRA is then a merge of epoch 3 (10%), 6 (70%), 9 (12%) and 18 (8%). After that I resized it with a factor of 0.96, target rank 32 resulting in the ~40MB file. As you can see in the percentages (of the epochs in the merge), good LoRA results were already achieved relatively early.

Training was done on a rented 3090 (cloud). Should you have any additional questions, feel free to ask.

这是群星再世第五十四期，以后会不定期出去世的群星Lora，以纪念他们。

对于刘家良的名号，喜爱动作港片的观众一定都不陌生。刘家良的父亲刘湛，是林世荣的徒弟、黄飞鸿的徒孙。自幼跟随父亲习武的刘家良，也练得了一身好武艺。1953年，16岁的刘家良进入影坛发展。凭借一身武艺，他成为了剧组的一名动作指导。60年代中期，随着邵氏电影的崛起，刘家良也进入了邵氏，并成为了当时名噪一时的动作指导。《独臂刀》三部曲、《大刺客》、《刺马》等电影的动作场景，都是由刘家良设计的。

1975年，刘家良在方逸华的支持之下转型导演。而他的处女作《神打》，也成为了港产功夫喜剧的奠基之作。而后的《中华丈夫》、《少林三十六房》、《十八般武艺》、《少林搭棚大师》等经典，也让刘家良坐稳了自己导演的位子。七十年代的电影银幕之上，刘家良备受好评，八、九十年代的港片中，他也有不少经典。李连杰的《南北少林》、周润发的《老虎出更》，都是出自刘家良导演之手。

刘家良2013年因病去世，享年79岁。

items.name: LECO - LegLength&Muscular
items.description:
This LECO was created for personal enjoyment as well as LECO practice.

The girls portrayed by our beloved AI are very attractive, but sometimes (or often) have body shapes that are just too beautiful. Long legs and toned bodies, for example.

But to put it simply, I prefer girls with shorter legs and softer bellies.

With this LECO, depending on the model, the legs will be a bit shorter and the muscle more modest.

The effect on the painting style is limited, but in return the effect is not too intense, so try it like a seasoning.

I recommend about 1.5 to 2.

Conversely, a negative value(such as -2) can beautifully enhance the character's physical appearance.

It is up to you how to use it!

By the way, I think this may work for men as well as women, but I don't know because I haven't tried it.

The same applies to realistic models, so please let me know the result if you like. (This LECO was trained on an anime-type model, so maybe it won't work.)

Then again, this is the result of a simple test, so perhaps there is still room for improvement.

Please let me know if there is anything I can do to help!

Have fun!

Edit:

Sorry, I uploaded the wrong file.

1.0b is the official version.

items.name: Pharma Bro (Martin Shkreli)
items.description:
High Quality Dreambooth (JP repo) trained model of the pharmaceutical sensation Martin Shkreli (aka "Pharma Bro"). Created using recent hi-resolution images via popular media.

Trigger with "Pharmabro Person"

(yes, put person also). Use "Hi-Res fix" with the settings you'd normally use for best results. Use prompt weighting and/or Controlnet to get maximum flexibility out of this likeness model. Trained locally using JP's repo (24gb VRAM req / arguably the best for likenesses).

Why a full checkpoint/2GB model for 1 subject?

Simply because the trained checkpoint gives you the best quality to start w/. LoRAs are fantastic for lots of things, but for human likenesses they don't match up to Dreambooth trained checkpoints.

"I need a LoRA for my workflow!"

It's easy to extract a LoRA from an SD checkpoint on your own if you prefer a LoRA for your workflow. For instance you can use the Auto1111 extension "Supermerger" to extract a LoRA. That said, LoRA will not match the quality of the original Dreambooth model (loss incurred).

Some samples images were generated w/ Controlnet for initial guidance and thus won't be reproducible exactly with only metadata (don't think Civitai lists whether or not CN was used).

items.description:
This LoRA is inspired by the intricate and delicate lines and structures of spider webs, using the vivid network structure of spider webs to create a dreamlike architectural design with imaginary spider silk. The irregular and varied grids and textures in the spider web are transformed into different facades, volumes, angles, and structures in the generated model, like a cleverly woven spider web, ultimately presenting extraordinary visual effects.

items.name: Raven the Trickster
items.description:
This Lora is based off of the character Raven the Trickster from the episode Heritage in the show Gargoyles.

The Lora runs well on a weight of 0.85 to the default of 1, as well as, the standard default settings for Steps and CFG Scale. Personally I like how it turns out when set to 50 Steps. Setting the Lora weight to 0.85 lets other Checkpoint styles set in more, which changes the look of the character. Keeping it at a default of 1 allows a more consistent look to the original character.

Using Checkpoints that tend to do humans and not anthropomorphic characters leads the results to show results vastly different from the raven headed character, such as a human head and humanoid body.

While the term 'Raven' should be well and good enough to cause the Lora to work more, adding the terms 'red eyes', 'wings', and 'loin cloth' permits a much more consistent look. Not adding 'loincloth' results in the loincloth to be remade into briefs or other clothing. Not adding 'wings' may permit and potentially not show wings.

Since the character was drawn in a simplified anatomy that was common in the Gargoyles show, adding the terms like 'muscular' and 'abs' would show abs that looks more like just lines along the stomach area than abs for the Lora when set at a weight of 1. Decreasing the weight would let the abs show more volume more often.

建议搭配特定的画师或者风格tag使用

Clip和采样器设置取决于主模型

版本选择:

KZ版:目前为止最好的版本,也是最推荐使用的版本

HT版:效果还行,就是有点过拟合

其他较老的版本:不建议使用

一些碎碎念:

几个月前刚接触c站,想找找有没有少卿的模型,结果没有.我以为应该很快就会有人训练出来了,结果几个月过去了也没有......于是就倒腾了一下午把模型整出来了.

由于网上能用于训练的资源很少,所以前几个模型都比较粗糙,后来我用粗略训练出的模型生成了一堆质量参差不齐的图片,挑出了一些相似度比较高的加入了训练集来训练新的模型,迭代了数次后才训练出了效果还不错的模型,中间有很多版本都废弃了.不得不说训练模型是真的好麻烦(´ཀ`」 ∠)

平时要上课基本没什么时间来炼丹，有时候模型练出来了会自己先玩几天再发，就当测试效果，有空的话会继续完善模型的
